man.htm|website=Box Office Mojo|accessdate=1 June 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170725120010/http://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=wonderwoman.htm|archive-date=July 25, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n| $821.8 million<ref>{{cite web|title=Wonder Woman (2017)|url=http://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=wonderwoman.htm|website=Box Office Mojo|accessdate=3 June 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170725120010/http://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=wonderwoman.htm|archive-date=July 25, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''[[Justice League (film)|Justice League]]''\n| Zack Snyder\n| '''Story by''' Chris Terrio & Zack Snyder<br />'''Screenplay by''' Chris Terrio and [[Joss Whedon]]\n| {{based on|''[[Justice League]]''|[[Gardner Fox]]}}\n| Warner Bros. / RatPac Entertainment / Atlas Entertainment / Cruel and Unusual Films\n| $300 million\n| $657.9 million<ref>{{cite web|title=Justice League (2017)|url=http://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=dcfilm1117.htm|website=Box Office Mojo|accessdate=5 December 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171119174046/http://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=dcfilm1117.htm|archive-date=November 19, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 2018\n| ''[[Teen Titans Go! To the Movies]]''\n| [[Aaron Horvath]] & Peter Rida Michail\n|'''Screenplay by''' Aaron Horvath & [[Michael Jelenic]]\n|{{based on|''[[Teen Titans]]''|[[Bob Haney]] and [[Bruno Premiani]]}}<br />{{Based on|''[[Teen Titans Go! (TV series)|Teen Titans Go!]]''|Aaron Horvath and Michael Jelenic}}\n| Warner Bros. / [[Warner Bros. Animation]]<ref name=\"insight-Feb2018\">{{cite web|url=https://www.varietyinsight.com/print_featurefilm_releases.php|title=Film releases|work=[[Variety Insight]]|accessdate=May 9, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180205105405/http://www.varietyinsight.com/print_featurefilm_releases.php|archive-date=February 5, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n| $10 millio