la-dc-comics/|archive-date=April 21, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nPaid services: [[Google Play]], [[ComiXology|Comixology]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.engadget.com/2013/10/08/dc-comics-and-vertigo-google-play/|title=DC Comics and Vertigo graphic novels arrive on Google Play, Sandman and all|website=Engadget|access-date=2017-04-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170421091118/https://www.engadget.com/2013/10/08/dc-comics-and-vertigo-google-play/|archive-date=April 21, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n{{Portal|United States|Comics|New York City|Companies}}\n{{Wikipedia books|DC Comics}}\n* [[September 17#Holidays and observances|Batman Day]] (September 17)\n* [[DC Cosmic Cards]]\n* [[DC Collectibles]]\n* [[List of DC Comics characters]]\n* [[List of comics characters which originated in other media]]\n* [[List of current DC Comics publications]]\n* [[List of films based on DC Comics]]\n* [[List of television series based on DC Comics]]\n* [[List of video games based on DC Comics]]\n* [[Publication history of DC Comics crossover events]]\n* [[List of unproduced DC Comics projects]]\n*[[DC Films]]\n*\n\n==Notes==\n{{Reflist|group=n}}\n\n==Citations==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==Sources==\n{{refbegin}}\n* {{cite book |last=Goulart |first=Ron |authorlink=Ron Goulart |title=Ron Goulart's Great History of Comics Books |publisher=Contemporary Press |location=Chicago |year=1986 |isbn=0-8092-5045-4 |ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book |authorlink=Gerard Jones |last=Jones |first=Gerard |title=Men of Tomorrow: Geeks, Gangsters, and the Birth of the Comic Book |url=https://archive.org/details/menoftomorrowgee0000jone |url-access=registration |publisher=Basic Books |year=2004 |isbn=0-465-03657-0 |ref=harv}}\n{{refend}}\n\n==External links==\n{{sisterlinks|d=Q2924461|c=category:DC Comics|wikt=Appendix:DC Comics|n=Category:Comics|v=no|b=no|s=no|voy=no|m=no|mw=no|species=no}}\n* [https://www.dccomics.com Dc Comics Official website]\n* {{gcdb publisher|i